Are Polish people aware of the steak we Americans (and the French?) call Filet MIGNON?  It comes from (what we Americans call) the beef tenderloin.  It's exceptionally tender, but not the most flavorful cut of beef.  It's a fairly small steak, hence its sense of being "dainty".

(A Google search tells me that the French use "Filet MIGNON" to refer to a cut from the pork tenderloin, not the beef.)

