French was used in fancy Polish restaurants in the 1920s and 1930s. Obviously everything changed after 1945, and we never went back to using French in gastronomy. So no, I don't think most Polish people are aware of filet mignon. I think I heard or saw it before, but Rhine came much more naturally to me than that. Also, I like eating at restaurants, but not ones with tablecloths and stuck up waiters, so I don't go to places that serve dainty steaks 🤣.

